# Stateless Component Scaffold Rule

## Trigger

Creating any new directory under:

- `src/frontend/components/core/**`
- `src/frontend/components/common/**`
- `src/frontend/components/logical-units/**`

## Generated Files

| File                      | Purpose                                                          |
| ------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `MyComponent.tsx`         | Arrow-function React component (stateless)                       |
| `MyComponent.stories.tsx` | Storybook demo (wrapped in ThemeProvider) **+** interaction test |
| `MyComponent.test.tsx`    | Unit test (Vitest)                                               |
| `MyComponent.styles.ts`   | styled-components (theme-aware)                                  |
| `index.ts`                | Barrel export                                                    |

## Template Snippets

`MyComponent.tsx`

```tsx
/** Renders <MyComponent>. */
import type { FC } from "react";
import { memo } from "react";
import type { MyComponentProps } from "./MyComponent.types";
import { Box } from "@/components/ui/box";
import { Typography } from "@/components/ui/typography";

export const MyComponent: FC<MyComponentProps> = memo(({ title }) => (
  <Box data-testid="my-component">
    <Typography variant="h6">{title}</Typography>
  </Box>
));
```

`MyComponent.types.ts`

```ts
export interface MyComponentProps {
  /**
   * Localized title text.
   * Provided by parent for i18n.
   */
  title: string;
}
```

`index.ts`

```ts
export * from "./MyComponent";
```

`MyComponent.stories.tsx`

```tsx
import { ThemeProvider } from "@mui/material/styles";
import { theme } from "@/themes";
import type { Meta } from "@storybook/react";
import { MyComponent } from "./MyComponent";

export default {
  title: "Core/MyComponent",
  component: MyComponent,
  decorators: [
    (Story) => (
      <ThemeProvider theme={theme}>
        <Story />
      </ThemeProvider>
    ),
  ],
} satisfies Meta<typeof MyComponent>;

export const Basic = {
  args: { title: "Hello 🌎" },
  play: async ({ canvasElement }) => {
    const c = within(canvasElement);
    await expect(c.getByText(/hello/i)).toBeVisible();
  },
};
```

## **Constraints**

- **No internal async/await** in event handlers.
- All styling via MUI sx or styled.
- Expose _all_ state via props **or** export a custom hook.
- JSDoc for every public prop / function, **no** type annotations inside comments.
- Consume design tokens via `useTheme` or the injected `theme` object from `src/themes`; never hard-code colors or spacings.
